Barlow Condensed Thin Regular (BarlowCondensed-Thin.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Barlow Condensed' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Thin' = NID 1 'Barlow Condensed Thin'.

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Barlow Condensed' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Thin Italic' = NID 1 'Barlow Condensed Thin' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Barlow Condensed ExtraLight Regular (BarlowCondensed-ExtraLight.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'BarlowCondensed-ExtraLight', Everything looks good.

Pass

Barlow Condensed ExtraLight Regular (BarlowCondensed-ExtraLight.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'BarlowCondensed-ExtraLight', Everything looks good.

Pass

Barlow Condensed ExtraLight Regular (BarlowCondensed-ExtraLight.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Barlow Condensed' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraLight' = NID 1 'Barlow Condensed ExtraLight'.

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Barlow Condensed' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraLight Italic' = NID 1 'Barlow Condensed ExtraLight' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'BarlowCondensed-Light', Everything looks good.

Barlow Condensed Light Regular (BarlowCondensed-Light.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Barlow Condensed' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light' = NID 1 'Barlow Condensed Light'.

Pass

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'BarlowCondensed-LightItalic', Everything looks good.

Barlow Condensed Light Italic (BarlowCondensed-LightItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Barlow Condensed' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light Italic' = NID 1 'Barlow Condensed Light' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

Barlow Condensed Regular (BarlowCondensed-Regular.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'BarlowCondensed-Regular', Everything looks good.

Barlow Condensed Regular (BarlowCondensed-Regular.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'BarlowCondensed-Regular', Everything looks good.

Pass

Barlow Condensed Medium Regular (BarlowCondensed-Medium.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Barlow Condensed' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium' = NID 1 'Barlow Condensed Medium'.

Barlow Condensed Medium Italic (BarlowCondensed-MediumItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Barlow Condensed' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium Italic' = NID 1 'Barlow Condensed Medium' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

Barlow Condensed Medium Italic (BarlowCondensed-MediumItalic.ttf)

Barlow Condensed SemiBold Regular (BarlowCondensed-SemiBold.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'BarlowCondensed-SemiBold', Everything looks good.

Pass

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.

NID 6 is 'BarlowCondensed-SemiBold', Everything looks good.

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Barlow Condensed' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold' = NID 1 'Barlow Condensed SemiBold'.

Barlow Condensed SemiBold Italic (BarlowCondensed-SemiBoldItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Barlow Condensed' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold Italic' = NID 1 'Barlow Condensed SemiBold' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Barlow Condensed Bold Italic (BarlowCondensed-BoldItalic.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'BarlowCondensed-BoldItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

Barlow Condensed ExtraBold Regular (BarlowCondensed-ExtraBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'BarlowCondensed-ExtraBold', Everything looks good.

Barlow Condensed ExtraBold Italic (BarlowCondensed-ExtraBoldItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Barlow Condensed' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraBold Italic' = NID 1 'Barlow Condensed ExtraBold' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

This font software is the property of Monotype Imaging Inc., or one of its affiliated entities (collectively, Monotype) and its use by you is covered under the terms of a license agreement. You have obtained this font software either directly from Monotype or together with software distributed by one of the licensees of Monotype. This software is a valuable asset of Monotype. Unless you have entered into a specific license agreement granting you additional rights, your use of this software is limited by the terms of the actual license agreement you have entered into with Monotype. You may not copy or distribute this software. If you have any questions concerning your rights you should review the license agreement you received with the software. You can learn more about Monotype by clicking here: www.monotype.com.

Barlow Condensed Black Regular (BarlowCondensed-Black.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Barlow Condensed' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Black' = NID 1 'Barlow Condensed Black'.

Barlow Condensed Black Italic (BarlowCondensed-BlackItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'BarlowCondensed-BlackItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

Unless you have entered into a specific license agreement granting you additional rights, your use of this software is limited by the terms of the actual license agreement you have entered into with Monotype. You may not copy or distribute this software. If you have any questions concerning your rights you should review the license agreement you received with the software. Barlow Condensed Black Italic (BarlowCondensed-BlackItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Barlow Condensed' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Black Italic' = NID 1 'Barlow Condensed Black' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass
